Module com.example.project3cs213
Package com.example.project3cs213

Class MemberDatabase

java.lang.Object
com.example.project3cs213.MemberDatabase
public class MemberDatabase extends Object
MemberDatabase class to store members inside a member list. Performs add and remove member, display members with or without order.
Author:
Songyuan Zhang, Ryan S. Lee, Robert Jimenez

  • Method Details

    • find

      private int find(Member member)
      Find the member from the database and return the index of the member. Find the member by traversing the member list.
      Parameters:
      member - member who needs to be found.
      Returns:
      index if the member is found, Compare.INDEXNOTFOUND otherwise.

    • grow

      private void grow()
      Grow capacity by 4 into new array and copy old array elements into the new array. Find the member from the database and return the index of the member. Find the member by traversing the member list.

    • loadMemberFromFile

      public void loadMemberFromFile(String fileName) throws FileNotFoundException
      Load members from a given filename that contains member information.
      Parameters:
      fileName - string that contains file name.
      Throws:
      FileNotFoundException - if file is not found.

    • add

      public boolean add(Member member)
      Add a member into the member list. Add member who is not already in the list. Grow the list when necessary.
      Parameters:
      member - member to add into the member list.
      Returns:
      true if the member is successfully added, false if member is already in the list.

    • remove

      public boolean remove(Member member)
      Remove a member from the member list. Remove a member who can be found in the list. After removing the member, move all subsequent members one space to the left.
      Parameters:
      member - member to remove from the member list.
      Returns:
      true if the member is successfully removed, false if member is not found in the list.

    • print

      public StringBuilder print(StringBuilder stringBuilder)
      Append all member information from the MemberDatabase to stringBuilder. Display the list of members in the database without sorting (current order in the array.). Corresponds to the P command from the GymManager class.
      Parameters:
      stringBuilder - stringBuilder to append membership information.
      Returns:
      stringBuilder with the latest information.

    • printByCounty

      public String printByCounty()
      Print all members from the MemberDatabase order by the county names and then the zip codes. If the locations are in the same county, ordered by the zip codes. Use insertion sorting algorithm. Corresponds to the PC command from the GymManager class.
      Returns:
      string with the latest information.

    • printByExpirationDate

      public String printByExpirationDate()
      Print the list of members in the database ordered by the expiration dates. If two expiration dates are the same, their order doesn’t matter. Use insertion sorting algorithm. Corresponds to the PD command.
      Returns:
      string with the latest information.

    • printByName

      public String printByName()
      Print the list of members in the database ordered by the members’ last names and then first names. If two members have the same last name, ordered by the first name. Use insertion sorting algorithm. Corresponds to the PN command from the GymManager class.
      Returns:
      string with the latest information.

    • printWithFee

      public String printWithFee()
      Print the list of members in the database with fees
      Returns:
      string with the latest information.

    • getMemberInformation

      public Member getMemberInformation(Member tempMember)
      Populate the expiration date and location of a member. Called by GymManager to populate the expiration date and location of a member, whose first name, last name, and date of birth are given.
      Parameters:
      tempMember - a temporary member who only has name and date of birth.
      Returns:
      member if the population is success, null otherwise.

    • checkExpirationDate

      public boolean checkExpirationDate(Member member)
      Check expiration date of a member has passed or not. Find the member and compare the expiration date with today's date. Called by GymManager to check the expiration date.
      Parameters:
      member - the member whose membership expiration date needs to be checked.
      Returns:
      true if the expiration date has passed, false otherwise.

    • isInDatabase

      public boolean isInDatabase(Member member)
      Check a member is the database or not. Called by GymManager to check the existence of a member in the database.
      Parameters:
      member - the member who needs to be found in the database.
      Returns:
      true if the member is found, false otherwise.

    • checkEmptyDatebase

      public boolean checkEmptyDatebase()
      Check the member database is empty or not.
